ZH: 陨石是在天空中坠落的岩石。
EN: Meteorites are rocks that fall from the sky.
ZH: 这块陨石重约500克。
EN: This meteorite weighs about 500 grams.
ZH: 那颗陨石在坠落时留下了一个巨大的坑。
EN: The meteorite left behind a huge crater when it fell.
ZH: 这片陨石的表面异常光滑。
EN: The surface of this meteorite is unusually smooth.
ZH: 陨石可以提供有关太阳系形成的信息。
EN: Meteorites can provide information about the formation of the solar system.
ZH: 这些陨石被认为是稀有的。
EN: These meteorites are considered rare.
ZH: 这块陨石来自月球。
EN: This meteorite is from the moon.
ZH: 陨石可以在地球上的不同地方发现。
EN: Meteorites can be found in different parts of the Earth.
ZH: 陨石通常有不同的形状和颜色。
EN: Meteorites usually have different shapes and colors.
ZH: 这个国家的博物馆有一块巨大的陨石展览。
EN: The museum in this country has a large exhibition of meteorites.
ZH: 学者们正在研究这个陨石中的化学成分。
EN: Researchers are studying the chemical composition of this meteorite.
ZH: 这个陨石的年龄估计为4.5亿年。
EN: The age of this meteorite is estimated to be 450 million years.
ZH: 大约有4000年前，人们就开始收集陨石了。
EN: People started collecting meteorites about 4000 years ago.
ZH: 这颗陨石被发现于一座古老的火山口中。
EN: This meteorite was discovered in an ancient volcanic crater.
ZH: 陨石的研究可以为地质学家提供很多信息。
EN: The study of meteorites can provide a lot of information for geologists.
ZH: 这批陨石被运送到实验室进行分析。
EN: This batch of meteorites is being transported to the laboratory for analysis.
ZH: 陨石的形成与太空中的碰撞有关。
EN: The formation of meteorites is related to collisions in space.
ZH: 这块陨石来自一个远离地球的星系。
EN: This meteorite is from a galaxy far away from Earth.
ZH: 这个小村庄的居民幸运地发现了一块陨石。
EN: The residents of this small village were lucky to find a meteorite.
ZH: 这颗陨石被认为来自行星间的碰撞。
EN: This meteorite is believed to come from collisions between planets.
